description.narrative:
New/additional funds to mitigate the impact of COVID-19
The objectives and expected results of the Core Activities are:

1. To strengthen feminist movements at local, national and regional levels particularly of the most marginalized; 
2. To amplify the influence, impact and voice of Asia Pacific women’s rights advocates in local, national, regional and global policy setting bodies; 
3. To facilitate the production of evidence based research and tools for advocacy outcomes and movement building 
4. To build the capacities of women’s rights organizations and movements in the region using rights based perspectives and interrogating the intersection of patriarchy, globalization, fundamentalisms and militarization.
